You will live by the sword and serve your brother;
but when you grow restless,
you will break free from his control.”

“Benjamin is a ferocious wolf.
He devours his prey;
in the evening, he divides the spoil.”

Sisera came to Jael’s tent and asked for water,
but she gave him milk;
she brought him buttermilk in a beautiful bowl.

Please deal gently with me, YAHWEH;
show me mercy, for I’m sick and frail and weak.
Heal me, YAHWEH, for I’m falling apart.

if I have wronged someone at peace with me,
if I have betrayed a friend, repaying evil for good,
or if I have unjustly harmed my enemy

They refuse to slander or insult others;
they’ll never listen to gossip or rumors,
nor would they ever harm a friend with their words.

The way you counsel me makes me praise you more,
for your whispers in the night give me wisdom,
showing me what to do next.

He rescues me from my enemies;
he lifts me up high and keeps me out of reach,
far from the grasp of my violent foe.

Every time they cried out to you in their despair,
you were faithful to deliver them;
you didn’t disappoint them.

Escort me into your truth; take me by the hand and teach me.
For you are the God of my salvation;
I have wrapped my heart into yours all day long!

In mercy you have seen my troubles, and you have cared for me;
even during this crisis in my soul I will be radiant with joy,
filled with praise for your love and mercy.

You have kept me from being conquered by my enemy;
you broke open the way to bring me to freedom,
into a beautiful, broad place.

Human strength and the weapons of man
are false hopes for victory;
they may seem mighty, but they will always disappoint.

Then my fears will dissolve into limitless joy;
my whole being will overflow with gladness
because of your mighty deliverance.

Don’t let these proud boasters trample me down;
don’t let them push me around
by the sheer strength of their wickedness.

I’m like a deaf man who no longer hears.
I can’t even speak up, and words fail me;
I have no argument to counter their threats.

I’m like a deaf man who no longer hears.
I can’t even speak up, and words fail me;
I have no argument to counter their threats.

I confess all my sin to you; I can’t hold it in any longer.
My agonizing thoughts punish me for my wrongdoing;
I feel condemned as I consider all I’ve done.

So let the people of Zion rejoice with gladness;
let the daughters of praise leap for joy!
For God will see to it that you are judged fairly.

For wisdom will come from my mouth;
words of insight and understanding will be heard
from the musings of my heart.

But I am like a flourishing olive tree, anointed in the house of God.
I trust in the unending love of God;
his passion toward me is forever and ever.

Though many wish to fight and the tide of battle turns against me,
by your power I will be safe and secure;
peace will be my portion.

My strength is found when I wait upon you.
Watch over me, God, for you are my mountain fortress;
you set me on high!

He alone is my safe place;
his wraparound presence always protects me.
For he is my champion defender;
there’s no risk of failure with God.
So why would I let worry paralyze me,
even when troubles multiply around me?

Your visitations of glory bless the earth;
the rivers of God overflow and enrich it.
You paint the wheat fields golden as you provide rich harvests.

All the earth will bow down to worship;
all the earth will sing your glories forever!
Pause in his presence

Everyone will say, “Come and see the incredible things God has done;
it will take your breath away!
He multiplies miracles for his people!”

O Lord, we have passed through your fire;
like precious metal made pure,
you’ve proved us, perfected us, and made us holy.

For my people will be the conquerors;
they will soon have you under their feet.
They will crush you until there is nothing left!”

O God, my King, your triumphal processions
keep moving onward in holiness;
you’re moving onward toward the Holy Place!

Let all who seek my life be humiliated and confused.
God, send them sprawling, all who wish me evil;
they just want me dead.

The sun and moon will stop shining
before your devoted lovers will stop worshiping;
for ages upon ages the people will love and adore you!

Distant kings will surrender and come with their gifts
from every continent and coastland;
they will offer their tribute to you.

It will be an instant end to all their life of ease;
a blink of the eye and they’re swept away by sudden calamity!
They’re all nothing more than momentary monarchs

Remember your promises to us,
for darkness covers the land,
giving the violent ones a hiding place.

Storm clouds filled with water high in the skies;
cloudbursts and thunderclaps announced your approach.
Lightning-flashes lit up the landscape.

The heavenly winds of miracle power blew in their favor,
and food rained down upon them;
succulent quail quieted their hunger as they ate all they wanted.

The heavenly winds of miracle power blew in their favor,
and food rained down upon them;
succulent quail quieted their hunger as they ate all they wanted.

Revive us, O God! Let your beaming face shine upon us
with the sunrise rays of glory;
then nothing will be able to stop us.

God, there’s no one like you;
there’s no other god as famous as you.
You outshine all others, and your miracles make it easy to know you.

We can do nothing but leap for joy all day long,
for we know who you are and what you do,
and you’ve exalted us on high.

We’ve been overwhelmed with grief;
come now and overwhelm us with gladness.
Replace our years of trouble with decades of delight.

O Lord our God, let your sweet beauty rest upon us.
Come work with us, and then our works will endure;
you will give us success in all we do.

It’s true the wicked flourish, but only for a moment;
they foolishly forget their destiny with death,
that they will all one day be destroyed forevermore.

Nothing could ever change your royal decrees;
they will last forever!
Holiness is the beauty that fills your house;
you are the one who abides forevermore!

Everyone come meet his face with a thankful heart.
Don’t hold back your praises;
make him great by your shouts of joy!

Within their branches you provide for birds
a place to build their nests;
even herons find a home in the cypress trees.

For the earth’s overseer has the power to make it tremble;
just a touch of his finger and volcanoes erupt
as the earth shakes and melts.

Then Joseph was put in charge of everything under the king;
he became the master of the palace
over all the royal possessions.

Let’s exalt him on high and lift up our praises in public;
let all the people and the leaders of the nation know
how great and wonderful is YAHWEH, our God!

Yet he himself will drink from his inheritance
as from a flowing brook;
refreshed by love he will stand victorious!

The Lord will never forget us in our need; he will bless us indeed!
He will bless the house of Israel;
he will bless the house of Aaron, his priest.

Your displeasure rests with those who are arrogant,
who think they know everything;
you rebuke the rebellious who refuse your laws.

Help me turn my eyes away from illusions
so that I pursue only that which is true;
drench my soul with life as I walk in your paths.

Your tender mercies are what I need, O God;
give me back my life again
through the revelation of your judgments.

Your promises are the source of my bubbling joy;
the revelation of your Word thrills me
like one who has discovered hidden treasure.

This is where the thrones of kings have been established
to rule in righteousness;
even King David ruled from here.

There is no such thing as darkness with you.
The night, to you, is as bright as the day;
there’s no difference between the two.

You even formed every bone in my body
when you created me in the secret place;
carefully, skillfully you shaped me from nothing to something.

For they strengthen you inside and out
and inspire you to do what’s right;
you will be energized and refreshed by the healing they bring.

There is a spirit named Foolish,
who is boisterous and brash;
she’s seductive and restless.

When an evil man dies, all hope is lost,
for his misplaced confidence goes in the coffin,
buried along with him.

True lovers of God are filled with longings
for what is pleasing and good,
but the wicked can only expect doom.

So don’t be drawn in by the hypocrite,
for his gracious speech is a charade,
nothing but a masquerade covering his hatred and evil on parade.

Lord, you have abandoned your people, the house of Jacob,
for they are full of occultic secrets from the east,
like the land of the Philistines, with sorcerers everywhere;
they are pleased with what is false and foreign.

Their land overflows with gold and silver;
they are wealthy beyond measure.
Their land is filled with horses and innumerable chariots!

So the Lord will afflict the foreheads
of the daughters of Zion with scabs;
YAHWEH will make the front of their heads bald in that day.”

Cries of mourning will be heard at the city gates;
with the anguish of such great loss,
she will sit down and grieve in the dirt.

He will lift up a banner to signal the distant nations;
he whistles for them to come from the ends of the earth.
Look! Here they come, running swiftly and speedily!

The Assyrian army attacked Aiath;
they passed over into Migron
and stored their equipment at Michmash.

The cities of Heshbon and Elealah cry out;
their voices are heard as far away as Jahaz;
even the bravest warriors of Moab are shaken to the core.

So now Moab will wail;
everyone will wail over the ruin of their country.
Lament and grieve for the foundations of Kir-Hareseth.

I will give over the Egyptians into the hands of a cruel master;
a brutal king will rule over them,” says the sovereign God,
the Lord YAHWEH, Commander of Angel Armies.

Zoan’s elite have become utter fools;
the nobles of Memphis are utterly deceived,
and Egypt has been led astray by her tribal chiefs.

The ground itself mourns and withers;
the soil languishes over the sins of its people,
and the wealthy elite wither and languish.

Riots break out because there is no wine.
The sun has set on their gladness and joy;
celebrations have disappeared from the earth.

and like the heat of a drought in a desert land;
but you subdued the heat under the shade of clouds.
You alone silence the song of tyrants.

Perfect, absolute peace surrounds those
whose imaginations are consumed with you;
they confidently trust in you.

For he has said to them,
“This is your rest, so let the weary rest;
this is your comfort”—but they would not listen.

Egypt’s help is utterly worthless;
that’s why I nicknamed her
Rahab, the Do-Nothing Dragon.

Cattle and young bulls will also be slain;
their land will be drenched with blood
and the dust soaked with fat.

Night and day it will never be extinguished;
its smoke will go up forever and ever.
Through the endless ages it will lie desolate;
no one will pass through it forever.

The grass withers, the flower fades
when the breath of YAHWEH blows upon it;
the people are just like grass!

The islands see it and panic;
the ends of the earth tremble;
they approach and draw near.

Take off your pretty veil;
take two millstones and grind grain.
Lift your skirt, bare your legs, and wade through the rivers.

With my mighty hand I laid the foundation of the earth;
with the span of my right hand I spread out the cosmos.
And when I speak to them, they both stand at attention.

And he said to me,
“Israel, you are my special servant;
in you I will be glorified.”

For this is what YAHWEH has to say:
“You were sold for nothing;
now you will be redeemed without any payment.”

Burst into joyous songs, you rubble of Jerusalem!
For YAHWEH has graciously comforted his people;
he has become the Kinsman-Redeemer of Jerusalem!

Just as many were appalled at the sight of him
(for so marred was his appearance, like an object of horror;
he no longer looked like a man)

Like wayward sheep, we have all wandered astray.
Each of us has turned from God’s paths and chosen our own way;
even so, YAHWEH laid the guilt of our every sin upon him.

By coercion and with a perversion of justice
he was taken away.
And who could have imagined his future?
He was cut down in the prime of life;
for the rebellion of his own people,
he was struck down in their place.

No one seeks true justice;
no one pleads his case with honesty.
They rely on their illusions and misleading lies;
they conceive trouble and give birth to sin.

“For I, YAHWEH, have spoken:
‘The whole land will remain desolate;
however, the end of the world is not yet.

“From the smallest to the greatest,
they are greedy for corrupt profits;
prophet and priest alike, they all practice deceit.

YAHWEH, there is no God like you;
you are unrivaled in your greatness and might!
The power of your name is so great!

My own inheritance has turned against me
like savage, roaring lions in the jungle;
therefore, I will deal with her as though I hate her.

Many destroyers have marched over those barren hills.
YAHWEH’s sword has devoured the people throughout the land;
no one is safe.

For the sake of your great name, do not disown us;
do not dishonor Jerusalem, that glorious place from which you rule.
Don’t break your promise; remember your covenant with us.

There is nothing more deceitful than the heart of man;
who can understand it?
Man’s heart is sick, in need of healing.

YAHWEH, you alone are my praise.
Heal me, and I will be perfectly healed;
save me, and I will be completely saved.

YAHWEH says:
“Your wound is incurable;
your injuries are so serious, they’re beyond healing.

When he comes to invade, he will defeat Egypt:
“ ‘Those destined for the plague will die by the plague;
those destined for captivity will go into captivity;
those destined for the sword will die by the sword.

Therefore I wail for Moab;
I cry out for the whole country,
and I mourn for the people of Kir Hareseth.

Pronounce this parable for these rebels: ‘Lord YAHWEH says to you:
“ ‘Put a cooking pot on the fire;
put it on and fill it with water.

“Praise be to the exalted Lord God of Israel,
for he has seen us through eyes of grace,
and he comes as our Hero-God to set us free!
